---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '@/components/ui/PageHeader.astro';
import TimeSyncGate from '@/components/react/TimeSyncGate.tsx';
import Formula from '@/components/ui/Formula.astro';
import Callout from '@/components/ui/Callout.astro';
import DocRef from '@/components/ui/DocRef.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Time synchronisation gate"
  description="Why an OSNMA receiver must know the time before it can trust a tag."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="5 · The receiver"
    title="The time synchronisation gate"
    lead="TESLA's security rests on one assumption: a key was still secret when its tag arrived. The receiver enforces that with a loose time check before any tag is trusted."
  />

  <p>
    OSNMA authenticates data with a key that is only revealed later. That trick
    works only if the receiver can be sure the key was <em>not already public</em>
    at the moment it received the tag. A receiver whose clock runs far ahead of
    real time could accept a key that is, in fact, already disclosed — and a
    spoofer could exploit that to forge tags. The defence is a coarse but strict
    time check.
  </p>

  <h2>The requirement</h2>
  <p>
    The time-synchronisation requirement is <Formula tex="T_L = 30\text{ s}" />, one
    subframe <DocRef doc="rxg" section="2.1" />. For normal tags the receiver's
    clock uncertainty <Formula tex="B" /> must satisfy:
  </p>
  <Formula tex="B < \tfrac{T_L}{2} = 15\text{ s}" display />
  <p>
    Slow MACs (ADKD = 12) carry an extra 10-subframe key delay, which buys more
    tolerance:
  </p>
  <Formula tex="B < \tfrac{T_L + 300}{2} = 165\text{ s}" display />

  <p>Move the slider to see which tags a receiver may use at a given uncertainty:</p>

  <TimeSyncGate client:visible />

  <h2>Where the time comes from</h2>
  <p>
    The receiver reads GST from the signal — I/NAV word type 0 or 5, or the
    Secondary Synchronisation Pattern — and checks it against its own clock
    <DocRef doc="rxg" section="5.3" />. It then derives the subframe time used in
    every key and tag computation:
  </p>
  <Formula tex="GST_{SF} = GST_0 + 30 \cdot \left\lfloor \tfrac{GST_{SIS} - GST_0}{30} \right\rfloor" display />

  <Callout type="security">
    <p>
      This is why a long-idle receiver must re-synchronise before authenticating:
      its clock has drifted, and until the uncertainty is back under 15 s the TESLA
      guarantee does not hold.
    </p>
  </Callout>
</BaseLayout>
